Review: Such a great movie with a great ending. Amy Steel and Deborah Foreman are both absolute icons who I wish I saw more from.

I don't care what anyone says. This is easily the best adaptation of I Am Legend! Something about that 70s feel is just so good with this movie. Not to mention it's super action packed and has such an underrated musical score. It does a really nice job as well with raising the question on who is the real villain.
I haven't read a book in a long time, but maybe Conan the Librarian can help me pick my next selection.

Movie: Winnie the Pooh: Blood and Honey
Review: I think this is exactly a one and done. I agree with many who said that it would be better if it was campy. No lie, I thought it was supposed to be people dressed as Pooh and Piglet since they look like Halloween costumes (yeah, I know this is the case in real life), but like... I didn't know that was what they actually looked like until I watched the movie. Not to mention so many dumb decisions were made by the characters! Not a good movie at all.

Okay, this was hilarious! I was already quite invested with the first half hour or so, and then the rest of this movie truly made me appreciate the originality and creativity that went into this movie. All for a super low budget too!
The 2000sification of Just One of the Guys.
Definitely an uncomfortable watch, but it was also a well done movie! The pseudo-documentary style really played into that uncomfort level nicely.

I mean, this was not the worst movie ever like people made it out to be, but it wasn't good by any means either. It honestly feels like nothing happened. Very CGI heavy with weak fight scenes. With that being said, I am interested to see what they continue doing with whatever Spiderman universe this is.

I... can't believe i wasted 2 hours of my life with thatðŸ¤£ it felt so disjointed, it was absolutely boring, and Chris Macneil's role was pointless. I will say some of the effects were pretty good though, but that's about it. How the hell are they going to follow up with two more movies?
Jesse is correct in saying that Jaws has one of the best film scores of all time.

I don't care what anyone says. This is an underrated John Carpenter film! Sure, it has a little bit of consistency problems with trying to figure out if it was a pure sci-fi or a comedy movie, but it was pretty neat otherwise. The special effects and music are top notch in this, and I honestly didn't entirely mind Chevy Chase as the main character! It was different, and I appreciated it.
Everyone has at least one problematic fave. This one happens to be mine.
